  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "SUPERVISOR",
  "description": "<p>The restaurant supervisor must ensure that the restaurant is neat and presentable, as the restaurant's appearance directly influences customer perception of the establishment's quality. A restaurant head captain ensures that all centerpieces are on the tables properly and that linens, silverware and glasses are clean.</p><p>Restaurant captains often have a managerial role. It is their job to ensure all hosts and waiters are adequately trained, informed of the restaurant's policies and knowledgeable about menu items and daily specials.</p><p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>· Help achieve financial targets.</p><p>· Lead the team during shifts and ensure we maintain our service standards.</p><p>· Hand out menus, answer questions, and offer recommendations.</p><p>· Set tables and keep the restaurant clean.</p><p>· Serve food and drinks.</p><p>· Follow guidance from managers.</p><p>· Help with cleaning tasks.</p><p>· Perform other duties assigned by management.</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p>· Ability to work effectively in a fast-paced, high-stress environment.</p><p>· Proven problem-solving skills.</p><p>· Strong leadership abilities, including the capacity to build relationships and manage staff at all levels.</p><p>· relevant qualification and experience<br /></p><p>We thank you for your interest and we regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified. All resumes received will be used for recruitment purposes only.</p><p>EA License ID: 18C9520</p><p>EA Registration ID: R1765753</p>",
